"v.离题 【英】 v.离题(to depart temporarily from the main subject) 【考】 stray : group / digress : subject(离群离开群体/离题 离开主题)digress : excursive / reiterate : redundant(离题的特点是离题的 /反复说的特点是多余 的) 【记】 di+gress(走)→走离 →离题 【例】 She digressed and forgot what she was originally talking about. v. 离题(脱离写作或演说主题) = stray 【记】di脱离, gress走－走脱离了主题－离题 【类】stray: group = digress: subject[topic] = detour: route离群离开群体 = 离题离开主题 = 绕路而行离开路线digress: excursive = reiterate: redundant离题是离题的 = 反复说是多余的aside: digression = summary: excerpt离题话: 离题 = 摘要: 摘录(同义) 【记】dis 离开 + gress 走开 【相关】aggress 向前走→进攻，congress(走到一起)聚会,degressive(下走)下降，digress(分开走)离题，ingress(向里走)入口，egress(向外走)出口，progress (前走)前进，regress (回走)退回，retrogress (回走)退步，transgress (穿过走)越界 digress (v.)  1520s, from Latin digressus, past participle of digredi ""to go aside, depart"" (see digression), or perhaps a back-formation from digression. Related: Digressed; digressing."
